        "content": "<p>How do you formalize this result? \"Let (X, d) be a metric space and A be a subset of X. Then, (A, dA) where dA = d on A x A is a metric space.\"</p>\n<p>I can do</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">SubsetMetricSpace</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hX</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MetricSpace</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">MetricSpace</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">eq_of_dist_eq_zero</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a₁</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a₂</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MetricSpace</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">eq_of_dist_eq_zero</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n</code></pre